OL,3,CPensioners 'have been biggest winners
OL,4,Cfrom tax and benefit changes since
OL,5,C2010'
OL,7,FPensioners have gained more than
OL,8,Fworking-age households from tax and
OL,9,Fbenefit decisions since 2010,
OL,10,Faccording to a think tank.
OL,12,FThe average pensioner is #900 better
OL,13,Foff as a result of benefit policy
OL,14,Fchanges since 2010 while the average
OL,15,Fnon-pensioner household is #1,400
OL,16,Fworse off amid a less generous social
OL,17,Fsecurity system for working-age
OL,18,Ffamilies, the Resolution Foundation
OL,19,Fsaid.
