OL,3,CPensioners 'have been biggest winners
OL,4,Cfrom tax and benefit changes since
OL,5,C2010'
OL,7,FDespite state pension age rises, the
OL,8,Fnumber of people claiming the state
OL,9,Fpension went up by around 570,000,
OL,10,Ffrom 12.4 million to 13 million,
OL,11,Fbetween 2009-10 and 2024-25, and is
OL,12,Fexpected to rise to 13.2 million by
OL,13,F2028-29.
OL,15,FThe demographic shift has meant that a
OL,16,Fgreater share of public spending,
OL,17,Fincluding the state pension, other
OL,18,Fpensioner benefits and old-age health
OL,19,Fspending, is focused on this older
OL,20,Fcohort, the foundation said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
