OL,7,FSophie Hale, principal economist at
OL,8,Fthe Resolution Foundation, said: "The
OL,9,Fcombination of Britain's big baby
OL,10,Fboomer generation retiring, and
OL,11,Fpolicies that have benefited
OL,12,Fpensioners the most, has meant that
OL,13,Fthe profile of Britain's public
OL,14,Fspending has greyed.
OL,16,F"Overall pensioners have gained more
OL,17,Fthan working-age households from tax
OL,18,Fand benefit decisions since 2010,
OL,19,Fwhile families with children have seen
OL,20,Fsupport fall by #780 a year."
